			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I like how my post on how to block the ads was quietly erased without so much as an explanation.  I guess the new look comes with spiffy censorship of polite posts.<BR>
<BR>
Well, I'll be back reposting it every 10 minutes unless I am banned.  If you want to censor me childishly, I will post childishly.<BR>
<BR>
Folks, if you want to block the bulk of the ads, go into you /etc/hosts file (UNIX) or $WINDOWS/system32/drivers/etc/hosts file (Windows OSs) and put the following:<BR>
<BR>
127.0.0.1	ads.musiccity.com<BR>
127.0.0.1	www.adready.net<BR>
127.0.0.1	ad.trafficmp.com<BR>
127.0.0.1	ads.doubleclick.net<BR>
127.0.0.1	ad.doubleclick.net<BR>
127.0.0.1	mediamgr.ugo.com<BR>
<BR>
save and close the file.  The effect should be almost immediate, although you may have to close and restart any browsers that were open when you made the change.
				</font>
